    <h3>Key person at Yoga Essentials</h3>
    <p>Prathima Yarlagadda (RYT 500 and RYT 200) has dedicated herself to the yoga practice, study of yoga since discovering its joys and benefits in 2005. She trained in the disciplines of Ashtanga (BNS Iyengar), Sivananda (Swami Sivananda, India) and Traditional (A.L.V Kumar) combining elements of these styles into a dynamic and inspiring alignment-based flow. She and her loving husband Sree Surapaneni have studied Vipassana meditation and incorporate its teachings of awareness into life. In 2014, Prathima co-taught a class for children from economically weaker sections of the society in rural India. She creates a safe, non-competitive space for her students to dive beneath the surface of their daily lives to find deeper meaning and inspiration. She offers detailed verbal cues and expert hands on adjustments/assists to help his students find a fuller experience in their yoga practice. Her classes offer creative sequences with intentional themes, emphasizing the importance of proper alignment, pranayama breathing techniques, mindfulness, and meditation. Modification and advanced options are made available for new students and experienced yogis so that all can reach their potential. She is honored to teach yoga, helping to bring balance, awareness, health, and happiness into other's lives.</p>
